definition: to fizzle out/to come to nothing
to say/to tell/to announce/to report/to denounce/to file a lawsuit/to sue
to blow/to play a wind instrument/to blast/to puff/to boast/to brag/to end in failure/to fall through

sentences.english: And a cola he quaffed named Fenhuang fizzled.
sentences.chinese: 一种他大口大口喝的可乐被称为“风花告吹”。

sentences.english: Another such injury will put the kibosh on his athletic career.
sentences.chinese: 再受一次这样的伤，就会使他的运动事业告吹。
她和牙医师的约定告吹了。

sentences.english: The plan fizzled out for lack of money.
sentences.chinese: 计划由于缺钱最终告吹。

sentences.english: It's impossible if you stick to the rules.
sentences.chinese: 如果你坚持按规矩办事，那这事就得告吹。

sentences.english: The big industrial plan was scuttled.
sentences.chinese: 大办工业的规划告吹了。

sentences.english: But, kiss many times, disrelish him because of the woman short and fail.
sentences.chinese: 可是，相了好几次亲，都因为女方嫌他矮而告吹。

sentences.english: The project foundered as a result of lack of finance.
sentences.chinese: 该项目因缺乏资金而告吹。

definition: to part on bad terms/(of a meeting etc) to break up in discord
to come to a decision/to fix on (a date etc)/to determine/to finalize/to nail down (a deal etc)
to settle a matter by leaving it unsettled/to end up with nothing definite
to die peacefully/(fig.) to result in failure (without any outside interference)/to come to nothing/to fizzle out
to rush to conclude a matter/to end up abruptly
to terminate an agreement/to cancel a contract
to dawdle/to go slow deliberately/to fizzle out/to have all one's hopes dashed/(Tw) to have a soak in a hot spring
to have a falling out/to have a big argument
